data.description: Welcome to this timeless brick 2 story home located in the heart of the City of Union Point, GA.  This charming home is large and spacious, boasting 3180 square feet of living space, with 5 bedrooms and 3.5 tile baths, and with second story bedroom balconies overlooking Stewart Ave.  As you enter the home from the 25X4 covered front porch, you enter into the large beautiful front foyer, with black and white tiled floors with the staircase. The formal living room is to the right with herringbone hardwood floors. a fireplace, and very spacious aera (22X13.5). The dining room flows well from the living room with the same beautiful herringbone hardwoods floors and is (17.5X14).  The great room and the kitchen and sunroom are located off the back of the home. The great room is also spacious (22.5X13.5) with exposed beam ceilings, a masonry fireplace with gas logs and a gas starter. The beautiful eat-in kitchen overlooks the patio sunroom and boasts gen air appliances, and the same back and white tile flooring as in the foyer.  As you step outside from the great room into the sunroom you'll discover a delightful level well-manicured back yard, brick patio, and fully brick fencing that is a perfect area for relaxing or entertaining guests. Additionally, there's a outside work shed and a spacious 2 car 20X19 carport.  This exceptional residence enjoys close proximity to Atlanta just a 1.5-hour drive, and Augusta which is just a one-hour drive. Athens is also easy and convenient and only 45-minute away. Furthermore, the beautiful Lake Oconee is a mere 15-minute journey, offering access to some of the state's best recreational activities and fishing opportunities available anywhere.
